I like to focus on is just process improvement and automation. There's so much that we can do

00:03:54.119 --> 00:04:01.559
with code that sometimes it's like, I guess I always refer to it as treadmill work, where you're

00:04:01.559 --> 00:04:07.160
kind of sprinting in place, but never really getting progress. And so, a lot of what I like

00:04:07.160 --> 00:04:12.279
to focus on is how do we get, how do we automate this treadmill work where we can, so that we can

00:04:12.279 --> 00:04:18.920
kind of focus on the actual fun problems that data science can help solution for. Yeah, the fun

00:04:18.920 --> 00:04:24.679
problems. And lately I've been sort of like offering up some topics that I know that our

00:04:24.679 --> 00:04:29.079
guests like to talk about. And I think that's something really funny from when I was prepping

00:04:29.079 --> 00:04:35.160
with you, Dave, was that there are these topics that I was like, oh, these are sort of like

